Package pkgView

Class CarouselView

java.lang.Object
javafx.scene.Node
javafx.scene.Parent
javafx.scene.layout.Region
javafx.scene.layout.Pane
javafx.scene.layout.FlowPane
pkgView.CarouselView
All Implemented Interfaces:
javafx.css.Styleable, javafx.event.EventTarget
Direct Known Subclasses:
DragDropCarouselView, InfoCarouselView, SelectCarouselView
public abstract class CarouselView
extends javafx.scene.layout.FlowPane
Author:
- Zane Greenholt CarouselView class holds the basic functionality of a carousel object. These carousels display limited ranges of a List at one time, and the List can be traversed by using the left and right buttons. As the name suggests, the carousels can be imagined as circular and loop back around to the start of the list when the end is reached.

  • Constructor Details

    • CarouselView

      public CarouselView()
      CarouselView is abstract and each child has different implementations so the constructor initializes nothing.

  • Method Details

    • rotateLeft

      public void rotateLeft()
      Method that is called when the left button in a carousel is pressed. This will shift the focus of the carousel one index to the left, or to the highest index if the index becomes negative.

    • rotateRight

      public void rotateRight()
      Method that is called when the right button in a carousel is pressed. This will shift the focus of the carousel one index to the right, or to zero if the index surpasses the list size.

    • openInfoPopUp

      public void openInfoPopUp​(View view, javafx.scene.image.ImageView img, java.lang.String name, java.lang.String sciName, int numLeps, int dollars, java.lang.String description, java.util.List<java.lang.String> leps)
      Part of the handler for opening a popup screen when an image is clicked. It has plant data passed into it from the controller to be displayed.
      Parameters:
      view - The program's view that is only initialized once
      img - The same image that was clicked
      name - The common name of the plant that had its image clicked
      sciName - The scientific name of the plant that had its image clicked
      numLeps - The number of lep species supported by the plant that had its image clicked
      dollars - The price of the plant that had its image clicked
      description - A short description of the plant that had its image clicked
      leps - A list of scientific names of the leps supported by a host plant

    • update

      public void update()
      The update method properly displays the VBox's that are held in the carouselView. This method is called any time the carousel is rotated or the list of VBox's is altered, so that the user can see the correct images at all times.
